Class Structure:
================

Main Class:
    LuftrauserGame - class
Objects:
    AAirplane -Abstract Class
    UserAirplane -class extends AAirplane
    EnemyAirplane -class extends AAirplane
        ~has an IAirplaneAI to determine actions
    AShip -Abstract Class
	~has an IShipAI to determine actions
    SmallShip -class extends AShip
    MediumShip -class extends AShip
    LargeShip -class extends AShip
    
Thomas edit {

i would suggest:
    Actor - abstract class
    	Airplane - abstract class extends Actor
    		Big/Small/Special/User -extends Airplaine
    	Ship - abstract class extends Actor
    		Big/Small/Special -extends Ship
    		
    Actor has methods like these:
    	abstract void act()
    	abstract void draw()
    	
    	void move(x, y)
    	void target(Actor)
    	void lookAtTarget()
    	void shootAtTarget(AmmoType)
    	void setAI(AI)
    	boolean hasCooldown()
    	
    	
    why?
    
    Because all ships float on water, and thus behave like ships. 
    All airplanes can fly and have their own physics.
    
    Like this you can create simple AI:
    
    BasicAI implements AI
    
    	void act(Actor actor){
    		World world = actor.getWorld())
    		actor.lookAtTarget(world.getPlayer())
    		
    		if(!actor.hasCooldown()){
    			actor.shootAtTarget(AmmoType.BULLET);
    		}
    	}
    
    Ofcourse this is all very basic, but you can easily expand your game or modify your game like this.
}
AI's:
    IAirplaneAI -interface
    AirplaneAIWeak -class implements IAirplaneAI
    AirplaneAIMedium -class implements IAirplaneAI
    AirplaneAIStrong -class implements IAirplaneAI
    IShipAI -interface
    ShipAIWeak -class implements IShipAI
    ShipAIMedium -class implements IShipAI
    ShipAIStrong -class implements IShipAI
StateManagers:
    GameTickHandler -class
        updates all locations, etc.
    CollissionHandler -class
        checks for any collissions
    InputHandler -class
        checks for any user input
Other Classes:
    Graphics classes
    Projectile -class
    other?
